"smart_sources:000 Zettelkasten/Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells..md": {"path":"000 Zettelkasten/Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells..md","class_name":"SmartSource","history":[{"blocks":{"000 Zettelkasten/Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells..md#":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells..md#Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells. However, there are novel methods to overcome these barriers. [[Enhancing the tumor microenvironment (TME) from an immunologically unresponsive state (\"cold\") to an inflammatory and activated state (\"hot\") can boost the effectiveness of immunotherapy interventions.]] Additionally, [[One way to help increase tumour specificity is to incorporate additional receptors on the T-cell that operate as Boolean functions.]] By employing this approach, the risk of inadvertently targeting healthy tissue in the central nervous system (CNS) can be minimized, while simultaneously enhancing the specificity of targeting glioblastoma cells.{1}":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells..md#References":true},"mtime":1709479676974,"size":960,"hash":"114724af71b9fee16fa825d87356d2b2390b54eea623031befe0759422921d9f"}],"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.02376697,-0.01182249,-0.01762079,0.02835849,0.04819766,-0.01973118,0.02590791,-0.03551368,-0.02995295,0.00639751,-0.00643294,-0.0227588,-0.03814933,-0.04145901,0.0177542,0.00067776,0.04026631,0.01038181,0.01875911,-0.01561894,0.10370761,-0.0129634,0.00056382,0.02710689,-0.05340188,-0.01181409,0.01283056,0.00867967,-0.0801059,-0.05598502,-0.00346633,0.02492386,0.0415203,0.01539337,0.01953382,0.00055653,0.00671727,-0.00826011,0.00779017,-0.01777483,-0.03373556,-0.00833735,0.00316583,-0.00328992,0.01000494,0.05064927,0.03409943,0.00814199,0.00452354,0.04587967,-0.0192825,-0.01687192,-0.00318098,0.01554846,-0.04046061,-0.00959242,-0.01986803,-0.04861815,-0.0219153,-0.00530486,-0.00999361,-0.00743854,-0.14299867,0.26811254,0.00901387,0.00059349,0.01031017,-0.02538243,0.00649804,0.14388037,0.01120211,-0.0341778,0.00215413,0.00495105,-0.00798436,0.00143001,-0.04155479,0.01292173,0.02104576,0.02904452,0.11257128,-0.07914136,0.01925022,0.00262465,0.04217005,-0.00817524,-0.01754551,0.01232129,-0.02700741,-0.00604135,0.00501728,0.01691204,0.03462891,-0.0034248,0.21952327,0.00096903,-0.01934627,-0.05817864,0.0267282,0.06485974,0.01131545,-0.01235669,0.00694629,0.0449275,-0.03226314,0.00685802,0.00710529,0.0106419,0.03729584,-0.01569367,-0.02531043,0.01650304,-0.05412915,0.01546824,-0.00416051,0.01828513,-0.01480466,-0.01008792,0.00153328,0.09149737,0.00110228,-0.02232766,-0.01360147,0.01097194,-0.04064739,0.08092955,0.00005177,0.08795873,-0.01745132,0.03029877,-0.04483263,0.02407812,0.01837572,0.02164576,0.00137786,-0.01761548,-0.0018648,0.01938687,-0.04038921,0.00099964,-0.00494153,-0.11268871,-0.00101299,-0.11496384,-0.00049658,-0.10932118,0.00129031,-0.0147363,0.01565284,0.04123353,0.0063856,-0.00214567,0.01987546,-0.02668038,-0.0013837,-0.03450297,-0.02305511,0.17421237,0.02620194,-0.03228696,-0.00722886,0.01327253,0.02967815,0.13414598,-0.02201778,-0.03590145,0.01715837,-0.01774502,-0.03172074,0.01214344,-0.00486