"smart_blocks:000 Zettelkasten/Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells..md#Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells. However, there are novel methods to overcome these barriers. [[Enhancing the tumor microenvironment (TME) from an immunologically unresponsive state (\"cold\") to an inflammatory and activated state (\"hot\") can boost the effectiveness of immunotherapy interventions.]] Additionally, [[One way to help increase tumour specificity is to incorporate additional receptors on the T-cell that operate as Boolean functions.]] By employing this approach, the risk of inadvertently targeting healthy tissue in the central nervous system (CNS) can be minimized, while simultaneously enhancing the specificity of targeting glioblastoma cells.{1}": {"class_name":"SmartBlock","embeddings":{},"path":"000 Zettelkasten/Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells..md#Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells. However, there are novel methods to overcome these barriers. [[Enhancing the tumor microenvironment (TME) from an immunologically unresponsive state (\"cold\") to an inflammatory and activated state (\"hot\") can boost the effectiveness of immunotherapy interventions.]] Additionally, [[One way to help increase tumour specificity is to incorporate additional receptors on the T-cell that operate as Boolean functions.]] By employing this approach, the risk of inadvertently targeting healthy tissue in the central nervous system (CNS) can be minimized, while simultaneously enhancing the specificity of targeting glioblastoma cells.{1}","heading":"Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells. However, there are novel methods to overcome these barriers. [[Enhancing the tumor microenvironment (TME) from an immunologically unresponsive state (\"cold\") to an inflammatory and activated state (\"hot\") can boost the effectiveness of immunotherapy interventions.]] Additionally, [[One way to help increase tumour specificity is to incorporate additional receptors on the T-cell that operate as Boolean functions.]] By employing this approach, the risk of inadvertently targeting healthy tissue in the central nervous system (CNS) can be minimized, while simultaneously enhancing the specificity of targeting glioblastoma cells.","length":15,"lines":[4,12],"key":"000 Zettelkasten/Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells..md#Two of the main challenges to glioblastoma CAR T cell therapy are the immunosuppressive TME and inherent heterogeneity of single-target antigens expressed on its tumour cells. However, there are novel methods to overcome these barriers. [[Enhancing the tumor microenvironment (TME) from an immunologically unresponsive state (\"cold\") to an inflammatory and activated state (\"hot\") can boost the effectiveness of immunotherapy interventions.]] Additionally, [[One way to help increase tumour specificity is to incorporate additional receptors on the T-cell that operate as Boolean functions.]] By employing this approach, the risk of inadvertently targeting healthy tissue in the central nervous system (CNS) can be minimized, while simultaneously enhancing the specificity of targeting glioblastoma cells.{1}"},
